definition.value: A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of three N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine residues linked (1->4).
Peptide that acts as a mechanosensitive ion channel blocker.

A member of the class of  thiadiazoles  that is 1,3,4-thiadiazole substituted by pyrazin-2-yl and (2,6-dichlorobenzyl)sulfanediyl groups at positions 2 and 5, respectively. It is a selective activator of mechanosensitive channel piezo1.
A secondary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of (R)-salsolinol obtained by protonation of the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of (R)-N-methylsalsolinol obtained by protonation of the imino group; major species at pH 7.3.

An organosulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfate and neuraminosyl carboxy groups of 8-O-sulfo-alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-ceramide; major species at pH 7.3.
A trisaccharide consisting of alpha-L-fucose, beta-D-galactose and beta-D-glucose residues joined by sequential (1->2)- and (1->3)-linkages.
An indolyl pyrimidinamine compound resulting from the Sonogashira coupling of 10-bromo-6,7-dihydro-5H-pyrimido[5,4-c]carbazol-2-amine with 2-methylbut-3-yn-2-ol.
A secondary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of  norsalsolinol arising from the protonation of the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of phenylacetic acids that is phenylacetic acid in which the phenyl group is substituted by nitro, hydroxy and nitro groups at positions 3, 4 and 5 respectively.
A quaternary ammonium ion that is the  conjugate acid of 4-(trimethylammonio)butanoate.
A binuclear oxo-bridged Ru compound that selectively inhibits mitochondrial calcium uniporter mediated Ca(2+)-uptake with nanomolar potency in cells.
